  "text": "The data for the veterinary antibiotic sulfachloropyridazine (SCP) obtained in a field experiment in the United Kingdom are deemed useful to verify the soil concentration function [CITATION_1] . This field experiment was performed with spiked manure spread over a sand soil and a clay soil, and all terms in the model described above were controlled. Soil properties were as follows: clay soil: Ap horizon (0-37 cm) sand 43%, silt 32% clay 25%, pH 6.8, %o.c. 2.2; sand soil: Ap horizon (0-37 cm) sand 69%, silt 21% clay 10%, pH 6.6, %o.c. 1.3.",
